# Update README on Feature Changes

When you add a new user-facing feature or significantly change an existing one, update the **Features** section in `README.md` to reflect the change.

## Rules

- Add new features under the appropriate category heading (Download, Format & Quality, Subtitles, Chapters, Sections, Preview, Queue, Progress, Settings, System Integration, State Persistence).
- If no existing category fits, create a new `###` heading in a logical position.
- Keep descriptions concise and factual — describe what the feature does, not why it's great.
- Remove or update entries for features that have been removed or changed.
- Do not rewrite unrelated parts of the README when updating features.
